Fire on Tuesday gutted a five-storeyed building housing different businesses at Balogun market, Lagos Island. The fire started in the early hours of Tuesday. DAILY POST reports that fire servicemen are currently on the ground, making frantic effort to put out the inferno. As at the time of filing this report, the cause of the outbreak cannot be ascertained by our reporter. In a video retrieved by DAILY POST, shop owners were seen throwing their goods down from the unaffected parts of the building as others scampered for safety. See video below…   Happening Now: Fire outbreak at the popular Balogun Market , #Lagos Island A post shared by  nwachukwu john owen (@realjohn_owen) on Nov 5, 2019 at 2:51am PST  Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.